Package com.example.recipeoop_1.dto

Class RecipeDto

java.lang.Object
com.example.recipeoop_1.dto.RecipeDto
public class RecipeDto extends Object
Data Transfer Object (DTO) for representing recipe data, typically used for creating or updating recipes through API requests.

This class includes validation constraints for its fields to ensure data integrity when receiving recipe information from clients.

Since:
2025-05-14

    • title

      @NotBlank(message="Title is required") private @NotBlank(message="Title is required") String title
      The title of the recipe.

      Constraints:

      • NotBlank: Must not be null and must contain at least one non-whitespace character. Message: "Title is required".
      Example: "Chocolate Chip Cookies"

    • ingredients

      @NotEmpty(message="At least one ingredient is required") private @NotEmpty(message="At least one ingredient is required") List<String> ingredients
      A list of ingredients for the recipe. Each ingredient is a string.

      Constraints:

      • NotEmpty: The list must not be null and must contain at least one ingredient. Message: "At least one ingredient is required".
      Example: ["200g flour", "100g sugar", "100g chocolate chips"]

    • instructions
